<title type="html"><![CDATA[A few sprite questions...]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7108&amp;p=69197#p69197"><![CDATA[
8 sprites per scanline means 8 sprite-tiles, as you've named them. <br /><br />It is exactly 8. The 9th is the one that won't be displayed. Mario and 3 goombas standing on the ground would display fine. None of the four tiles that make a fourth goomba can be displayed at all in the same frame on the ground with the others and Mario. This is why games swap sprite priority each frame. (The flickering)<br /><br />There is no technical reason why Mario couldn't use a different one of the four palettes for each tile displayed that makes Fire Mario.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3504">Kasumi</a> — Thu Oct 28, 2010 1:16 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
