<title type="html"><![CDATA[A few sprite questions...]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7108&amp;p=69195#p69195"><![CDATA[
The 8 sprite limit: Does that refer to 8 sprites or 8 sprite-tiles?<br />For example, every sprite in SMB is at least 2 tiles wide so 4 sprites would contain at least 8 sprite-tiles.<br />Also is the limit &gt;8 (8 max) or &gt;=8 (7 max)?<br /><br />Color in sprites: Fire-Mario in SMB and Kunio in River City Ransom are approximately the same size, why does Fire-Mario only use 1 palette (red, white, flesh) for all 8 tiles in his sprite while Kunio uses 2 palettes (blue, black, flesh and white, black, flesh)? Is this just a design choice or is there a technical reason?<br /><br />(Note: I'm not actually working on an NES game, just trying to boost the authenticity of a retraux game im working on....sorry if these questions have obvious answers...i couldn't find the answer to these in any documentation i read though.)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4610">pigpen</a> — Thu Oct 28, 2010 12:47 am</p><hr />
